  <h2>Information we collect</h2>

  <p>
    Depending on how you interact with our services, we may collect the following categories
    of personal information:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Identity information</strong>:
      name, company name, username, identification information and other details required
      to establish or manage a business relationship.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Contact information</strong>:
      email address, postal address, telephone number and other communication details.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Contract and business information</strong>:
      project requirements, communications, agreements, non-disclosure agreements (NDAs),
      statements of work and other information necessary to provide freelance services.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Financial and fiscal information</strong>:
      billing information, invoices, payment records, tax identification information and
      information required for accounting and legal compliance.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Technical information</strong>:
      IP addresses, browser information, operating system information, device information,
      access logs and security-related information.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Security and compliance information</strong>:
      information necessary to prevent fraud, abuse, unauthorized access, money laundering,
      sanctions violations or other unlawful activity.
    </li>
  </ul>


  <h2>Why we collect information</h2>

  <p>
    We process personal information for the following purposes:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Providing, maintaining and improving our services.
    </li>

    <li>
      Communicating with clients and responding to requests.
    </li>

    <li>
      Preparing, negotiating and fulfilling contracts and agreements.
    </li>

    <li>
      Managing invoices, payments, accounting obligations and tax compliance.
    </li>

    <li>
      Protecting our services against fraud, abuse, unauthorized access and security threats.
    </li>

    <li>
      Performing legal and regulatory obligations, including applicable sanctions and
      compliance requirements.
    </li>
  </ul>


  <h2>Legal basis for processing</h2>

  <p>
    Under the GDPR, we process personal information based on one or more of the following
    legal grounds:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Contractual necessity</strong>:
      processing information required to provide services, negotiate agreements and fulfill
      contractual obligations.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Legal obligations</strong>:
      processing required for accounting, taxation, regulatory and compliance purposes.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Legitimate interests</strong>:
      protecting our services, preventing abuse, improving reliability and ensuring security.
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Consent</strong>:
      where consent is required for optional processing activities.
    </li>
  </ul>


  <h2>Non-disclosure agreements and confidential information</h2>

  <p>
    During freelance engagements, we may process confidential information provided by clients
    under contractual obligations, including NDAs. Such information is handled only for the
    purposes agreed upon with the relevant parties and is protected according to applicable
    contractual and legal requirements.
  </p>


  <h2>Sharing of information</h2>

  <p>
    We do not sell personal information. We may share information only where necessary,
    including with:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Service providers that support our operations, such as hosting, payment processing,
      accounting or communication providers.
    </li>

    <li>
      Professional advisors, where required for legal, financial or compliance purposes.
    </li>

    <li>
      Authorities or institutions where disclosure is required by law or necessary to comply
      with legal obligations.
    </li>
  </ul>


  <h2>International transfers</h2>

  <p>
    If personal information is transferred outside the European Economic Area (EEA), we take
    appropriate measures to ensure that the transfer complies with applicable data protection
    requirements.
  </p>


  <h2>Data retention</h2>

  <p>
    We retain personal information only for as long as necessary for the purposes described
    in this policy.
  </p>

  <p>
    Certain information may be retained for longer periods where required by law, including
    fiscal, accounting, contractual or compliance obligations.
  </p>


  <h2>Security</h2>

  <p>
    We apply appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal information
    against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, loss or destruction.
  </p>


  <h2>Your rights under GDPR</h2>

  <p>
    Depending on applicable law, you may have the following rights:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Right to access your personal information.</li>
    <li>Right to correct inaccurate information.</li>
    <li>Right to request deletion of your information.</li>
    <li>Right to restrict or object to certain processing activities.</li>
    <li>Right to request portability of your information.</li>
    <li>Right to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    You may exercise these rights by contacting us through the contact information provided
    on this website.
  </p>


  <h2>Right to lodge a complaint</h2>

  <p>
    If you believe your rights have been violated, you may contact the relevant data
    protection supervisory authority in your jurisdiction.
  </p>


  <h2>Changes to this privacy policy</h2>

  <p>
    We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our services,
    legal requirements or processing activities. The latest version will always be published
    on this page.
  </p>

